women, because I think a lot

00:31:47.290 --> 00:31:50.530
of times we let ourselves fall
into these really terrible traps

00:31:50.530 --> 00:31:52.720
about we're in competition
with each other,

00:31:52.720 --> 00:31:55.390
but it's like no, we're not.

00:31:55.390 --> 00:31:59.020
Like don't take this the
wrong way, but men suck.

00:31:59.020 --> 00:32:02.130
And they're like, like making
you think you're in competition

00:32:02.130 --> 00:32:05.960
with each other so they can
sell you body cream or sell you,

00:32:05.960 --> 00:32:09.230
you know, pimple cream,
or like make sure you're

00:32:09.230 --> 00:32:10.910
so busy fighting with each
other, you don't notice

00:32:10.910 --> 00:32:12.330
that they're taking everything.

00:32:12.330 --> 00:32:15.190
And so I wanted to talk
about that, like this idea

00:32:15.190 --> 00:32:16.990
of like a female friendship.

00:32:16.990 --> 00:32:19.740
And then also kind of like
poke fun at the YA trope

00:32:19.740 --> 00:32:25.100
of like the mean girl and the
girl who like, who torments her.

00:32:25.100 --> 00:32:28.200
Yeah, I just think, I just think
relationships with women are

00:32:28.200 --> 00:32:29.850
so like-- it took me
a really long time.

00:32:29.850 --> 00:32:32.590
So before I was a
writer, a long time ago

00:32:32.590 --> 00:32:34.070
when I was a little
baby, just, you know,

00:32:34.070 --> 00:32:37.310
I was in the Army, right?

00:32:37.310 --> 00:32:38.610
And every-- thank you.

00:32:38.610 --> 00:32:41.260
And every girl I knew
in the Army was not

00:32:41.260 --> 00:32:43.050
like other girls, right?

00:32:43.050 --> 00:32:44.930
But we were all there
together doing the same thing,

00:32:44.930 --> 00:32:46.560
suffering the same
things, right?

00:32:46.560 --> 00:32:49.710
So I really wanted to take
that trope and kind of stab it

00:32:49.710 --> 00:32:52.620
in the eye because we're
all just like other girls,

00:32:52.620 --> 00:32:55.160
which is why we should all try
to figure out some common ground

00:32:55.160 --> 00:32:56.460
and support each other.

00:32:56.460 --> 00:32:57.840
So that was my feminist
platform.

00:32:57.840 --> 00:33:00.400
Sorry. I'll put my soapbox away.

00:33:00.400 --> 00:33:01.700
&gt;&gt; Thank you so much.

00:33:01.700 --> 00:33:03.000
&gt;&gt; Justina Ireland:
You're welcome.

00:33:03.000 --> 00:33:04.300
All right, I have two minutes,

00:33:04.300 --> 00:33:05.600
so if anybody has any
one last question.

00:33:05.600 --> 00:33:07.680
We have time for
one last question.

00:33:07.680 --> 00:33:10.270
Go ahead.

00:33:10.270 --> 00:33:14.890
&gt;&gt; What's the best way to
convey emotion in your writing?

00:33:14.890 --> 00:33:16.600
&gt;&gt; Justina Ireland:
You would have

00:33:16.600 --> 00:33:19.140
to ask somebody who's actually
good at writing emotion.

00:33:19.140 --> 00:33:21.260
[ Laughter ]

00:33:21.260 --> 00:33:24.580
You're like, I read your book!

00:33:24.580 --> 00:33:25.880
You're lying!

00:33:25.880 --> 00:33:27.180
Thank you!

00:33:27.180 --> 00:33:29.400
For me, I don't write
emotion in the first draft.

00:33:29.400 --> 00:33:30.930
And the first draft
was mostly just events

00:33:30.930 --> 00:33:32.510
and people responding
to those events.

00:33:32.510 --> 00:33:34.820
Emotion comes later, when I
know where the story is going,

00:33:34.820 --> 00:33:37.080
and where I know where
the character arc is.

00:33:37.080 --> 00:33:39.030
I would say the best
way to buy emotion is

00:33:39.030 --> 00:33:41.060
to visualize the scene.

00:33:41.060 --> 00:33:42.490
What is the character
doing with their hands?

00:33:42.490 --> 00:33:43.790
Where are they moving?

00:33:43.790 --> 00:33:45.090
You know, like when I'm nervous,

00:33:45.090 --> 00:33:46.390
you can see I talk
with my hands, right?

00:33:46.390 --> 00:33:47.690
So I'm all up here with my
hands, like [inaudible].

00:33:47.690 --> 00:33:50.400
When I'm sad, I'm probably
looking down at the ground.

00:33:50.400 --> 00:33:53.050
So just think about like what
people do with their bodies

00:33:53.050 --> 00:33:54.490
when they're feeling
a certain way.

00:33:54.490 --> 00:33:56.580
I mean, you can tell me
you're sad, but if you say

00:33:56.580 --> 00:33:59.780
like her eyes were downcast
and her shoulders slumped,

00:33:59.780 --> 00:34:02.920
that conveys the emotion better
than saying, "I'm sad," right?

00:34:02.920 --> 00:34:04.930
So think about that physicality.

00:34:04.930 --> 00:34:06.540
So all right, you guys,
that's all I have.

00:34:06.540 --> 00:34:08.010
Thank you so much
for staying it out.

00:34:08.010 --> 00:34:09.520
[ Applause ]

